  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: edge-case coverage gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: This is a synthetic adversarial sample targeting the evidence-validity gap where validation samples cover only the nominal operating range and omit the high-shear-stress regions and low-flow near-stall conditions explicitly named in the COU intended use.",
