    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device, including high-shear-stress regions near the impeller blade tips and low-flow near-stall conditions at the design speed envelope boundary. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
