      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmark cases demonstrating correct implementation of governing equations at Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "Standard benchmark cases for rotating machinery (Taylor-Couette flow, lid-driven cavity) confirm correct implementation of the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver with MRF rotating reference frame treatment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study using Richardson extrapolation with GCI < 5% on primary QoI at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (3.2M, 8.1M, 18.4M elements) at the 3 L/min 3000 RPM nominal operating point yields GCI = 2.8% for hemolysis index. Mesh selected for all validation runs is the 8.1M element medium mesh, balancing accuracy and computational cost within the nominal operating range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated uncertainty at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro test conditions (blood analog fluid viscosity 3.2 cP, temperature 37°C, inlet pressure 10 mmHg) are documented and reproduced in simulation boundary conditions. Flow rates measured with Coriolis mass flowmeter (±1.5% accuracy). All five validation runs use conditions within the nominal 2–4 L/min, 3000–3500 RPM operating band."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of predicted and measured RH values with agreement within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "All five nominal validation points show predicted-to-measured RH agreement within 5%, which is within the combined uncertainty band (experimental ±5–7%, numerical discretization 2.8%). The validation metric V = (predicted − measured) / combined_uncertainty is less than 1.0 for all points, confirming adequate predictive agreement across the nominal range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated that simulated QoI (RH index) is the same quantity measured experimentally and used in the COU decision criterion at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is computed from the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle paths and compared directly against the ASTM F1841 normalised plasma free haemoglobin measurement. The same RH < 1 criterion is used in both the experimental acceptance test and the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities use geometry, fluid, and operating conditions sufficiently representative of the COU device and intended use at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments use the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump geometry with blood-analog fluid under CPB-relevant flow and speed conditions. The five nominal operating points span the central 2–4 L/min, 3000–3500 RPM clinical operating range. High-shear-stress blade-tip regions and near-stall low-flow conditions are noted as edge cases studied separately; that supplementary characterisation is not included in this evidence package but is referenced for completeness."
    },
