      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; literature justification of turbulence model selection is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published literature for rotating blood-contacting devices. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; nominal input values from literature and supplier specifications are sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties (density 1056 kg/m3, viscosity 3.2 cP) taken from ASTM F1841 blood-analog specification. Geometric inputs from pump technical drawing with nominal dimensions. Formal input uncertainty propagation not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sufficient number of validation test samples to characterise model performance across the intended operating range at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Five validation test points were collected spanning the nominal clinical operating range (2–4 L/min, 3000–3500 RPM). Each point was repeated three times to characterise experimental repeatability. The five-point matrix covers the central operating envelope with one boundary sample at 2 L/min 3500 RPM. This sample count is consistent with MRL 2 requirements for the nominal operating range."
    },
    {
